01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:41,610
Hello, handsome.

1023
01:20:19,147 --> 01:20:21,650
What's the name of your book?

1024
01:20:28,657 --> 01:20:32,626
What's the name of your book?

1025
01:20:32,661 --> 01:20:35,163
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1026
01:20:43,672 --> 01:20:48,176
"Truman Capote
read last night
before a packed audience

1027
01:20:49,678 --> 01:20:53,682
"from his nonfiction
book in cold blood.

1028
01:20:57,686 --> 01:21:01,189
"The true-crime novel
tells of killers
Richard Hickock

1029
01:21:01,690 --> 01:21:03,191
"and Perry Smith,

1030
01:21:04,693 --> 01:21:08,196
who brutally murdered
a Kansas family 3 years ago."

1031
01:21:10,198 --> 01:21:12,165
Wait, who sent that to you?

1032
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:14,167
That's not
your goddamn business.

1033
01:21:14,202 --> 01:21:16,704
It is my business,
because it's not true.

1034
01:21:16,739 --> 01:21:19,207
The organizers of
the reading needed a title.

1035
01:21:19,242 --> 01:21:21,174
They picked one,

1036
01:21:21,209 --> 01:21:23,712
a sensational one, I admit,

1037
01:21:23,747 --> 01:21:25,213
to attract a crowd.

1038
01:21:30,719 --> 01:21:32,721
They picked it?

1039
01:21:32,756 --> 01:21:33,722
Yes.

1040
01:21:35,223 --> 01:21:36,690
It's not your title.

1041
01:21:36,725 --> 01:21:39,227
Perry,
I haven't chosen one yet.

1042
01:21:40,729 --> 01:21:42,195
How could I choose a title

1043
01:21:42,230 --> 01:21:44,232
when we still haven't
talked about that night?

1044
01:21:44,733 --> 01:21:49,070
How could I?
I couldn't possibly.

1045
01:21:55,577 --> 01:21:57,579
You pretend to be my friend.

1046
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:00,081
I'm sorry.

1047
01:22:02,083 --> 01:22:04,085
I should have told you.

1048
01:22:05,086 --> 01:22:08,089
And I couldn't pretend
to be your friend

1049
01:22:09,591 --> 01:22:12,510
'cause the truth is,
I can't help wanting to be.

1050
01:22:17,515 --> 01:22:20,018
You don't have to
tell me anything...

1051
01:22:22,938 --> 01:22:24,940
if you don't want to.

1052
01:22:37,452 --> 01:22:38,954
I have something

1053
01:22:40,956 --> 01:22:42,457
from your sister.

1054
01:22:52,968 --> 01:22:54,469
She misses you.

1055
01:23:13,989 --> 01:23:15,490
Look at my belly.

1056
01:23:34,009 --> 01:23:37,796
There must be
something wrong with us,
to do what we did.

1057
01:23:49,808 --> 01:23:52,694
We heard there was
$10,000 in that house.

1058
01:23:53,695 --> 01:23:57,699
Once we tied up everybody
and searched all over,

1059
01:23:58,199 --> 01:24:00,701
I knew the guy
that told us about it was...

1060
01:24:00,736 --> 01:24:03,204
was wrong. There was...
there was no money.

1061
01:24:05,707 --> 01:24:07,957
Dick wouldn't believe it

1062
01:24:07,992 --> 01:24:09,994
so he went tearing
through the house,

1063
01:24:10,029 --> 01:24:11,763
banging on the walls

1064
01:24:11,798 --> 01:24:13,498
looking for a safe.

1065
01:24:18,002 --> 01:24:21,471
When he was done, he...

1066
01:24:21,506 --> 01:24:25,510
said he was gonna go up
to Nancy's room
and have his way with her.

1067
01:24:26,511 --> 01:24:28,513
I wouldn't allow it.

1068
01:24:29,514 --> 01:24:31,516
And I told him that.

1069
01:24:33,017 --> 01:24:34,519
So I sat with her.

1070
01:24:36,020 --> 01:24:37,487
Dick came up and got me.

1071
01:24:37,522 --> 01:24:42,026
We turned off the lights
and went down to the basement

1072
01:24:42,061 --> 01:24:44,529
where Mr. Clutter
and the boy was.

1073
01:24:48,032 --> 01:24:50,034
He kept saying,
"no witnesses," but I...

1074
01:24:51,536 --> 01:24:54,003
I figured
if I waited him out, he'd...

1075
01:24:54,038 --> 01:24:57,041
he'd give up
and we'd leave them
tied up there.

1076
01:24:57,542 --> 01:25:01,010
And we'd drive all night.
They'd never find us.

1077
01:25:01,045 --> 01:25:06,551
We tied Mr. Clutter's wrists
to a pipe over his head.

1078
01:25:06,586 --> 01:25:10,019
And he... he looked hurt,
so I cut him down.

1079
01:25:10,054 --> 01:25:14,058
I... I put a box out there
so he'd be more comfortable.

1080
01:25:17,061 --> 01:25:21,565
He asked how his wife
and daughter was
and I... I said they were fine,

1081
01:25:21,600 --> 01:25:26,070
and they were getting ready
for sleep, and it wouldn't
be long tili...

1082
01:25:26,105 --> 01:25:28,573
till morning
when they'd find him.

1083
01:25:37,081 --> 01:25:39,083
He was just looking at me.

1084
01:25:40,084 --> 01:25:42,086
Looking into my eyes.

1085
01:25:43,588 --> 01:25:47,056
Like he expected me
to kill him.

1086
01:25:47,091 --> 01:25:51,095
Like he expected me to be
the kind of person
who would kill him.

1087
01:25:58,102 --> 01:26:02,607
I was thinking,
"this... this nice man
is scared of me."

1088
01:26:08,112 --> 01:26:09,614
I was so ashamed.

1089
01:26:15,620 --> 01:26:19,123
I mean, I thought
he was a... a very nice...

1090
01:26:22,126 --> 01:26:23,127
gentle man.

1091
01:26:25,129 --> 01:26:28,132
And I thought so right up
till I slit his throat.

1092
01:26:34,138 --> 01:26:36,641
I didn't know what I did
till I heard the sound.

1093
01:27:31,579 --> 01:27:33,081
Added up,

1094
01:27:35,083 --> 01:27:38,586
how much money did
you get from the clutters
that night?

1095
01:27:43,091 --> 01:27:45,093
Between $40 and $50.

1096
01:29:48,833 --> 01:29:50,584
I mean, the truth is,

1097
01:29:50,619 --> 01:29:52,336
I’m desperate
to be done with it.

1098
01:29:54,839 --> 01:29:57,842
I've spent 4 years of
my life on this book.

1099
01:30:03,848 --> 01:30:06,350
They got a stay of executive
yesterday.

1100
01:30:07,351 --> 01:30:08,853
Another, yes.

1101
01:30:14,358 --> 01:30:15,860
Supreme court.

1102
01:30:18,362 --> 01:30:19,864
It's harrowing.

1103
01:30:22,867 --> 01:30:27,371
Me, all I want to do is
to write the ending
and there's no end in sight.

1104
01:30:42,887 --> 01:30:44,388
No, thank you.

1105
01:30:57,401 --> 01:30:58,868
"Dear friend Truman,

1106
01:30:58,903 --> 01:31:01,906
"haven't heard from you
in such a long while.

1107
01:31:01,941 --> 01:31:04,408
"Please help find new lawyer.

1108
01:31:05,409 --> 01:31:07,411
"If not,
Dick will have to write

1109
01:31:07,446 --> 01:31:09,413
"the supreme court brief
himself.

1110
01:31:11,415 --> 01:31:13,382
"Our last appeal.

1111
01:31:13,417 --> 01:31:15,419
"What a pair of
wretched creatures.

1112
01:31:15,454 --> 01:31:17,386
"Please help.

1113
01:31:17,421 --> 01:31:20,925
Your amigo? Perry."

1114
01:31:23,427 --> 01:31:25,429
Just put it with the others.

1115
01:31:54,876 --> 01:31:57,378
You know, at least for Nelle
you should...

1116
01:31:57,879 --> 01:32:00,882
you should try and pretend
you're having
a good time tonight.

1117
01:32:44,425 --> 01:32:46,427
I thought
I’d find you here.

1118
01:32:47,929 --> 01:32:49,430
Oh, Nelle.

1119
01:32:50,932 --> 01:32:51,898
Nelle.

1120
01:32:51,933 --> 01:32:53,434
Thank you.

1121
01:32:53,935 --> 01:32:55,937
I'll have another,
please.

1122
01:32:58,940 --> 01:33:00,191
How are you?

1123
01:33:00,226 --> 01:33:01,442
Terrible.

1124
01:33:02,944 --> 01:33:04,911
I'm sorry to hear that.

1125
01:33:04,946 --> 01:33:08,449
I mean,
it's torture the way...

1126
01:33:09,450 --> 01:33:11,452
what they're doing to me.

1127
01:33:16,457 --> 01:33:18,960
And now
it's the supreme court.

1128
01:33:19,961 --> 01:33:21,963
And can you believe it?

1129
01:33:23,965 --> 01:33:26,467
If they win this appeal,

1130
01:33:27,468 --> 01:33:28,970
I wili...

1131
01:33:29,971 --> 01:33:32,473
have a complete
nervous breakdown.

1132
01:33:34,475 --> 01:33:37,443
I may never recover,

1133
01:33:37,478 --> 01:33:41,482
and I’ll just pray
that it turns my way.

1134
01:33:44,485 --> 01:33:46,237
It must be difficult.

1135
01:33:46,272 --> 01:33:47,989
Oh, it's torture.

1136
01:33:49,490 --> 01:33:51,492
They're torturing me.

1137
01:33:52,493 --> 01:33:53,995
I see.

1138
01:33:58,499 --> 01:34:01,002
And how'd you like the movie,
Truman?

1139
01:34:17,518 --> 01:34:19,020
Yeah...

1140
01:34:23,524 --> 01:34:28,029
I frankly don't see
what all the fuss is about.

1141
01:35:14,291 --> 01:35:15,257
Hello.

1142
01:35:15,292 --> 01:35:16,794
Mr. Truman Capote?

1143
01:35:16,829 --> 01:35:17,760
Yeah.

1144
01:35:17,795 --> 01:35:20,047
I have a call
from Mr. Perry Smith

1145
01:35:20,082 --> 01:35:22,299
in the Kansas
correctional system.

1146
01:35:22,334 --> 01:35:24,301
Will you accept charges?

1147
01:35:25,302 --> 01:35:26,268
Yes.

1148
01:35:26,303 --> 01:35:28,305
Mr. Smith,
you're on the line.

1149
01:35:28,806 --> 01:35:29,807
Hello.

1150
01:35:31,809 --> 01:35:32,775
Hello?

1151
01:35:32,810 --> 01:35:34,777
Hello, Perry.

1152
01:35:34,812 --> 01:35:38,315
They let me make
a couple of phone calls
before I go down to holding.

1153
01:35:38,350 --> 01:35:41,819
Y-y-you heard
the supreme court
rejected the appeal?

1154
01:35:45,322 --> 01:35:47,825
No, I... I didn't.
I hadn't heard that.

1155
01:35:51,328 --> 01:35:52,830
Yeah.

1156
01:35:55,833 --> 01:35:57,334
I'm sorry.

1157
01:36:00,838 --> 01:36:03,340
Yeah. They let me make
2 phone calls.

1158
01:36:06,343 --> 01:36:09,847
We got a date set
for the warehouse,
Dick and me.

1159
01:36:11,348 --> 01:36:14,351
2 weeks and finito.

1160
01:36:14,852 --> 01:36:16,353
April 14.

1161
01:36:19,857 --> 01:36:21,859
Will you visit me?

1162
01:36:22,860 --> 01:36:24,361
Truman?

1163
01:36:51,889 --> 01:36:53,891
It's... it's him again.

1164
01:37:00,898 --> 01:37:03,901
It is utterly inappropriate
for me to talk to him.

1165
01:37:13,410 --> 01:37:14,411
Yes?

1166
01:37:19,416 --> 01:37:21,919
I'm sorry,
he won't be able to make it.

1167
01:37:34,765 --> 01:37:35,731
Hello?

1168
01:37:35,766 --> 01:37:37,733
Mr. Shawn, it's Nelle.

1169
01:37:37,768 --> 01:37:39,770
I just got this telegram.
Has he seen it?

1170
01:37:40,771 --> 01:37:42,738
He won't read it.

1171
01:37:42,773 --> 01:37:44,275
Would you put him on,
please?

1172
01:37:44,310 --> 01:37:46,242
Nelle, he won't talk.

1173
01:37:46,277 --> 01:37:50,781
Mr. Shawn,
if you have to hold him down
and put the phone on his ear,

1174
01:37:50,816 --> 01:37:52,783
I need to speak to him.

1175
01:37:54,285 --> 01:37:55,286
All right.

1176
01:38:12,303 --> 01:38:13,804
Um,

1177
01:38:15,806 --> 01:38:16,807
um,

1178
01:38:17,808 --> 01:38:19,310
it's Nelle.

1179
01:38:26,317 --> 01:38:27,818
Truman.

1180
01:38:29,270 --> 01:38:32,773
"Miss Nelle Harper Lee
and Truman Capote.

1181
01:38:34,775 --> 01:38:38,779
"Sorry that Truman
was unable to make it
here to the prison

1182
01:38:38,814 --> 01:38:42,166
"for a brief word
prior to necktie party.

1183
01:38:42,666 --> 01:38:45,634
"Whatever his reason
for not showin' up,

1184
01:38:45,669 --> 01:38:49,173
"I want him to know
that I cannot
condemn him for it.

1185
01:38:52,176 --> 01:38:54,643
"Not much time left,

1186
01:38:54,678 --> 01:38:58,182
"but want you both to know
that I’ve been
sincerely grateful

1187
01:38:58,682 --> 01:39:01,185
"for your friendship
through the years

1188
01:39:01,220 --> 01:39:04,153
"and everything else.

1189
01:39:04,188 --> 01:39:07,656
"I'm not very good
at these things.

1190
01:39:07,691 --> 01:39:11,195
"I have become
extremely affectionate
toward you both.

1191
01:39:12,196 --> 01:39:14,698
"But, harness time.

1192
01:39:16,200 --> 01:39:19,703
Adios, amigos.
Your friend, Perry."

1193
01:39:32,132 --> 01:39:35,135
Well, I didn't expect
to see you again.

1194
01:39:36,136 --> 01:39:38,639
You can visit
for a few minutes.

1195
01:39:42,643 --> 01:39:44,144
Yeah.
No.

1196
01:39:50,651 --> 01:39:52,152
5 minutes.

1197
01:39:55,656 --> 01:39:56,657
Well, well.

1198
01:39:58,659 --> 01:40:00,160
He returns.

1199
01:40:01,662 --> 01:40:04,164
I don't know
what you must think of me.

1200
01:40:06,166 --> 01:40:09,670
Well,
you haven't been foremost
on my mind lately,

1201
01:40:09,705 --> 01:40:11,672
as you can probably imagine.

1202
01:40:15,676 --> 01:40:17,177
You got the letter?

1203
01:40:19,680 --> 01:40:20,681
Yes, I did.

1204
01:40:24,685 --> 01:40:26,652
It's true.

1205
01:40:26,687 --> 01:40:28,689
I understand why you
didn't want to come.

1206
01:40:30,190 --> 01:40:33,193
I wouldn't be here either
if I didn't have to.

1207
01:40:33,228 --> 01:40:34,695
You got that right.

1208
01:40:39,199 --> 01:40:43,669
You know Ricardo
donated his eyes
to science?

1209
01:40:43,704 --> 01:40:48,208
Next week,
some blind man will be seeing
what Dick used to see.

1210
01:40:48,709 --> 01:40:51,211
Yeah, you could be
walking in Denver
or somewhere, Truman,

1211
01:40:51,712 --> 01:40:55,215
and suddenly these eyes
will be staring at you.

1212
01:40:55,250 --> 01:40:57,718
That would be something,
wouldn't it?

1213
01:40:58,719 --> 01:41:01,722
It would be. It would be.

1214
01:41:15,736 --> 01:41:17,738
You'll be watching?

1215
01:41:19,239 --> 01:41:20,741
I don't know, I’ll be...

1216
01:41:23,243 --> 01:41:24,745
do you want me to?

1217
01:41:29,750 --> 01:41:31,752
I'd like to have
a friend there.

1218
01:41:32,753 --> 01:41:35,255
Ok. Then I will.

1219
01:41:46,266 --> 01:41:47,768
It's all right.

1220
01:42:06,787 --> 01:42:08,789
I did everything I could.

1221
01:42:09,790 --> 01:42:10,791
It's ok.

1222
01:42:21,135 --> 01:42:22,636
I truly did.

1223
01:42:24,138 --> 01:42:25,556
I know.

1224
01:42:34,565 --> 01:42:35,566
It's time.

1225
01:42:46,076 --> 01:42:47,578
Mr. Capote.

1226
01:43:03,594 --> 01:43:05,060
Goodbye.

1227
01:43:05,095 --> 01:43:08,063
You're not rid of us yet.

1228
01:43:08,098 --> 01:43:09,850
We'll see you
in a few minutes.

1229
01:43:09,885 --> 01:43:11,602
I wish I had...
Mr. Capote.

1230
01:43:12,603 --> 01:43:14,605
Mr. Capote.
Goodbye.

1231
01:44:10,110 --> 01:44:11,612
Nice to see you.

1232
01:44:54,655 --> 01:44:56,622
Perry Edward Smith.

1233
01:44:56,657 --> 01:44:58,659
For the crime of murder
in the first degree,

1234
01:44:58,694 --> 01:45:00,160
by order of the cour
t of Finney county

1235
01:45:00,661 --> 01:45:02,663
and the supreme court
of the sovereign state
of Kansas,

1236
01:45:02,698 --> 01:45:04,164
you are sentenced
to hang until you die.

1237
01:45:04,665 --> 01:45:07,417
"I will fear no evil:
For thou art with me.

1238
01:45:07,452 --> 01:45:10,170
Thy rod and thy staff,
they comfort me."

1239
01:45:10,205 --> 01:45:12,172
You can say something
if you want.

1240
01:45:17,678 --> 01:45:20,180
Is there anybody
from the family here?

1241
01:45:21,181 --> 01:45:22,182
No, Perry.

1242
01:45:27,187 --> 01:45:28,689
Well, tell them...

1243
01:45:34,695 --> 01:45:39,199
I can't remember
what I was gonna
say for the life of me.

1244
01:45:57,718 --> 01:46:00,721
Our father who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

1245
01:46:01,221 --> 01:46:02,688
Thy kingdom come.

1246
01:46:02,723 --> 01:46:05,726
Thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.

1247
01:46:05,761 --> 01:46:08,193
Give us this day
our daily bread.

1248
01:46:08,228 --> 01:46:12,197
...as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

1249
01:46:12,232 --> 01:46:15,736
And lead us not
into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

1250
01:46:45,265 --> 01:46:47,768
It was a terrible experience

1251
01:46:50,771 --> 01:46:53,273
and I will never get over it.

1252
01:46:55,275 --> 01:46:58,779
They're dead, Truman.
You're alive.

1253
01:47:00,781 --> 01:47:04,284
And there wasn't anything
I could have done
to save them.

1254
01:47:07,287 --> 01:47:08,789
Maybe not,

1255
01:47:12,292 --> 01:47:14,795
but, the fact is,
you didn't want to.

